<article>
    <h1>Kamino Finance 2026 Guide: How to Lend, Borrow, and Earn Yield on Solana</h1>
    <div class="meta">
        <strong>Published:</strong> June 1, 2026 &bull; <strong>Read Time:</strong> 7 min &bull; <strong>Category:</strong> DeFi
    </div>

    <div class="toc">
        <h3>Table of Contents</h3>
        <ol>
            <li><a href="#what-is-kamino">What Is Kamino Finance?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#kamino-lend">Kamino Lend: Supply Assets & Earn APY</a></li>
            <li><a href="#kamino-borrow">Kamino Borrow: Use Collateral for Liquidity</a></li>
            <li><a href="#kamino-multiply">Kamino Multiply: Leveraged Yield Strategies</a></li>
            <li><a href="#kamino-vaults">Kamino Automated Vaults</a></li>
            <li><a href="#kamino-token">KMNO Token & Staking</a></li>
            <li><a href="#risks">Risks to Consider</a></li>
            <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>Key Takeaway:</strong> Kamino Finance has become Solana's leading lending protocol in 2026, with over $2.5B in total value locked. It offers lending, borrowing, leveraged Multiply strategies, and automated vaults ” making it a one-stop DeFi hub for passive income on Solana.
    </div>

    <h2 id="what-is-kamino">1. What Is Kamino Finance?</h2>
    <p>Kamino Finance is a decentralized lending and borrowing protocol built on Solana. Launched in 2023, it quickly became the go-to platform for Solana DeFi users thanks to its intuitive interface, competitive APYs, and innovative products like Multiply and automated liquidity vaults.</p>

    <p>Unlike traditional lending protocols, Kamino offers three core products under one roof:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Kamino Lend</strong> ” Supply tokens to earn variable APY</li>
        <li><strong>Kamino Borrow</strong> ” Borrow tokens against your deposited collateral</li>
        <li><strong>Kamino Multiply</strong> ” Leveraged exposure to yield-bearing positions</li>
        <li><strong>Kamino Vaults</strong> ” Automated yield optimization strategies</li>
    </ul>

    <p>In 2026, Kamino has expanded to support over 30 tokens including SOL, USDC, USDT, jitoSOL, mSOL, JUP, PYTH, and more. The protocol has survived multiple market cycles and continues to be the most liquid lending market on Solana.</p>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>Kamino by the Numbers (2026):</strong><br>
        &bull; $2.5B+ Total Value Locked<br>
        &bull; 30+ Supported Tokens<br>
        &bull; 500K+ Unique Lenders<br>
        &bull; 99.98% Uptime Since Launch
    </div>

    <h2 id="kamino-lend">2. Kamino Lend: Supply Assets & Earn APY</h2>
    <p>Lending on Kamino is the simplest way to earn passive income on your Solana assets. Here's how it works:</p>

    <div class="step-box" style="counter-set: step 0;">
        <strong>Connect Your Wallet</strong> ” Use Phantom, Backpack, or Solflare to connect to <a href="https://app.kamino.finance" target="_blank" rel="noopener">app.kamino.finance</a>.
    </div>
    <div class="step-box">
        <strong>Select a Pool</strong> ” Choose a token to supply (SOL, USDC, USDT, jitoSOL, etc.).
    </div>
    <div class="step-box">
        <strong>Set Amount & Approve</strong> ” Enter the amount and confirm the transaction in your wallet.
    </div>
    <div class="step-box">
        <strong>Earn APY</strong> ” Your supplied tokens earn interest that accrues in real-time, compoundable at any time.
    </div>

    <h3>Current Lending APYs (June 2026)</h3>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Token</th>
                <th>Supply APY</th>
                <th>Borrow APY</th>
                <th>Utilization</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>SOL</td><td>4.2%</td><td>6.8%</td><td>62%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>USDC</td><td>8.5%</td><td>11.2%</td><td>76%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>USDT</td><td>9.1%</td><td>12.0%</td><td>78%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>jitoSOL</td><td>5.8%</td><td>8.4%</td><td>69%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>mSOL</td><td>5.5%</td><td>8.1%</td><td>68%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>JUP</td><td>6.7%</td><td>10.5%</td><td>64%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>PYTH</td><td>3.9%</td><td>7.2%</td><td>54%</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    <p style="font-size:0.85em;color:#666;"><em>APYs are variable and change based on pool utilization. Check <a href="https://app.kamino.finance" target="_blank" rel="noopener">app.kamino.finance</a> for live rates.</em></p>

    <div class="pro-tip">
        Stablecoins (USDC, USDT) consistently offer the highest lending APYs due to higher borrowing demand. Supplying stablecoins on Kamino is one of the safest ways to earn 8-10% APY on Solana.
    </div>

    <h2 id="kamino-borrow">3. Kamino Borrow: Use Collateral for Liquidity</h2>
    <p>Kamino allows you to borrow tokens by depositing collateral. This is useful for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Getting liquidity</strong> without selling your crypto (tax-efficient)</li>
        <li><strong>Leveraging positions</strong> ” borrow more assets to amplify returns</li>
        <li><strong>Shorting</strong> ” borrow tokens to sell, hoping to buy back cheaper</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Loan-to-Value (LTV) ratios vary by asset. SOL typically allows 75% LTV, while stablecoins allow up to 85%. If your LTV exceeds the liquidation threshold, your collateral can be liquidated.</p>

    <div class="risk-box">
        <strong>Liquidation Risk:</strong> Always maintain a healthy LTV ratio below 65%. Use Kamino's built-in alerts to monitor your positions. A sudden market drop can trigger liquidation in seconds on Solana.
    </div>

    <h2 id="kamino-multiply">4. Kamino Multiply: Leveraged Yield Strategies</h2>
    <p>Kamino Multiply is one of the most popular features on the platform. It lets you create leveraged positions in a single click ” like a leveraged staking position or a leveraged liquidity pool position.</p>

    <h3>Popular Multiply Strategies</h3>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Strategy</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Typical APR Range</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>SOL ×3 Leveraged Stake</td><td>Borrow SOL �™ stake as jitoSOL �™ redeposit �™ repeat up to 3x leverage</td><td>12-18%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>USDC-USDT LP ×2</td><td>Deposit into Meteora DLMM pool with 2x leverage</td><td>15-25%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SOL-USDC LP ×2</td><td>Leveraged concentrated liquidity on Orca or Meteora</td><td>20-40%</td></tr>
            <tr><td>jitoSOL-SOL ×3</td><td>Leveraged liquid staking delta-neutral position</td><td>8-14%</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="warning">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Multiply strategies amplify both gains AND losses. A 10% drop in the underlying asset can result in a 30% loss at 3x leverage. Only use Multiply if you fully understand the risks.
    </div>

    <h2 id="kamino-vaults">5. Kamino Automated Vaults</h2>
    <p>Kamino Vaults are automated, actively managed DeFi strategies. Each vault has a specific strategy that rebalances positions to maximize yield while managing risk. In 2026, Kamino offers vaults for:</p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Liquid Staking Optimization</strong> ” Automatically routes SOL to the best liquid staking token (jitoSOL, mSOL, bSOL) based on APY</li>
        <li><strong>Stablecoin Yield</strong> ” Allocates USDC/USDT across lending pools and yield farms for maximum stablecoin APR</li>
        <li><strong>Delta-Neutral Strategies</strong> ” Earn funding rates and LP fees with minimal directional risk</li>
        <li><strong>Points Farming</strong> ” Automatically farms protocol points (Kamino KMNO, Jito JTO, etc.)</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="pro-tip">
        Kamino Vaults are ideal for passive investors who want DeFi yields without constant monitoring. The vault manager handles rebalancing, compounding, and risk management automatically.
    </div>

    <h2 id="kamino-token">6. KMNO Token & Staking</h2>
    <p>Kamino's native token, KMNO, is used for protocol governance and fee sharing. You can stake KMNO to earn:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>A share of protocol fees generated by Kamino Lend and Multiply</li>
        <li>Voting rights on protocol upgrades and parameter changes</li>
        <li>Potential airdrops and loyalty rewards</li>
    </ul>

    <p>KMNO staking currently offers approximately 6-10% APR paid in KMNO tokens plus a portion of the protocol's revenue.</p>

    <h2 id="risks">7. Risks to Consider</h2>
    <div class="risk-box">
        <strong>Smart Contract Risk</strong> ” While Kamino has been audited by multiple firms (OtterSec, Neodyme, Zellic), no smart contract is immune to bugs. Only invest what you can afford to lose.<br><br>
        <strong>Liquidation Risk</strong> ” On Solana, liquidations happen in seconds. If your borrow position nears the liquidation threshold, act fast or set up automated alerts.<br><br>
        <strong>Oracle Risk</strong> ” Kamino uses Pyth Network oracles. While Pyth is reliable, oracle manipulation attacks have occurred on other protocols.<br><br>
        <strong>Market Risk</strong> ” DeFi yields are variable. High APYs can quickly drop as more capital enters a pool or borrowing demand decreases.
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>Diversification Strategy:</strong> Don't put all your capital in one protocol. Consider splitting your DeFi deposits across Kamino (lending), Marginfi (borrowing), and Sanctum (liquid staking) for optimal risk-adjusted returns. Learn more in our <a href="/solana-defi-composability-money-legos-lending-staking-lp-2026.html">Solana DeFi Composability Guide</a>.
    </div>

    <h2 id="faq">8. Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>Is Kamino Finance safe?</h3>
    <p>Kamino has been audited by OtterSec, Neodyme, and Zellic. It has operated for over 2 years with no major exploits. However, always practice good security hygiene ” use a dedicated DeFi wallet, approve only necessary spending limits, and monitor your positions regularly.</p>

    <h3>What wallet works with Kamino?</h3>
    <p>Kamino supports Phantom, Backpack, Solflare, and WalletConnect-compatible wallets. For the best experience, use Phantom or Backpack on desktop or mobile.</p>

    <h3>How much can I earn lending on Kamino?</h3>
    <p>Lending APYs vary by token and utilization. Stablecoins (USDC/USDT) typically earn 7-10% APY, while SOL earns 3-6% APY. Check live rates on the Kamino app.</p>

    <h3>What's the difference between Kamino and Marginfi?</h3>
    <p>Both are lending protocols on Solana, but Kamino offers additional products like Multiply (leveraged positions) and automated vaults. Marginfi focuses on a simpler lending/borrowing experience with lower fees. For a full comparison, see our <a href="/solana-defi-deep-dive-best-protocols-lending-borrowing-yield-farming-2026.html">Solana DeFi Deep Dive</a>.</p>

    <h3>Can I use Kamino on mobile?</h3>
    <p>Yes! Kamino's web app works on mobile browsers. For the best mobile experience, use Phantom or Backpack's in-app browser to access app.kamino.finance.</p>

    <h3>What happens if Kamino gets exploited?</h3>
    <p>Kamino doesn't have an official insurance fund, but the team has been proactive about compensating users during minor incidents. For additional protection, consider diversifying across multiple lending protocols.</p>

